d%20me%20he%20thought%20he%20could%20get%20it%20done%20and%20that%20he'd%20call%20me%20back%20quickly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%20continued%20in%20the%20email%2C%20%26quot%3BAt%20this%20point%2C%20we%20should%20probably%20prepare%20for%20it%20to%20leak%20that%20we%20offered%20%246b%20for%20them%20and%20all%20the%20negative%20that%20will%20come%20from%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20under%20questioning%20by%20a%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20attorney%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20Zuckerberg%20said%20he%20thought%20Snapchat%20%26quot%3Bwasn't%20growing%20at%20the%20potential%20that%20it%20could%26quot%3B%20and%20believed%20he%20could%20make%20it%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20what%20it's%20worth%2C%20I%20think%20if%20we%20would%20had%20bought%20them%20we%20would%20have%20accelerated%20their%20growth%2C%20but%20that's%20just%20speculation%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20testified%20in%20a%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20federal%20courtroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20government%20introduced%20the%20email%20to%20try%20to%20bolster%20its%20argument%20that%20Zuckerberg's%20Meta%20sought%20to%20maintain%20its%20dominance%20in%20the%20social%20media%20market%20through%20acquisitions%20rather%20than%20competition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20testimony%2C%20Zuckerberg%20said%20Snapchat%20%26quot%3Bwas%20and%20is%20a%20meaningful%20competitor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20Zuckerberg's%20comments%20on%20how%20he%20says%20he%20could%20have%20improved%20the%20app%2C%20Snap%20spokesperson%20Monique%20Bellamy%20told%20Business%20Insider%3A%20%26quot%3BAnticompetitive%20behavior%20can%20often%20slow%20and%20thwart%20growth%20for%20smaller%20companies%20and%20startups%2C%20especially%20when%20dominant%20companies%20like%20Meta%20use%20their%20size%20and%20position%20to%20stifle%20competition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPublic%20reports%20of%20Meta's%20attempt%20to%20buy%20Snap%2C%20and%20then%20egregiously%20copy%20its%20features%2C%20wa